HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 154
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School on the
occasion of its seventy-fifth annual Tomato Festival
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School on the occasion of the
3 seventy-fifth Our Lady of Prompt Succor Tomato Festival.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and
5 School for its contributions to the Chalmette community and to commend it on the occasion
6 of the seventy-fifth Our Lady of Prompt Succor Tomato Festival; and
7 WHEREAS, the Our Lady of Prompt Succor Parish Tomato Festival began in 1951
8 and honors the Creole tomato, which is grown exclusively in the mineral-rich, alluvial soil
9 of St. Bernard and Plaquemines parishes; and
10 WHEREAS, the family-friendly Tomato Festival is a decades-long tradition that
11 benefits Our Lady of Prompt Succor Church and School, St. Bernard Parish's only Catholic
12 school, and helps fund renovations and upgrades; and
13 WHEREAS, the seventy-fifth Tomato Festival will be held from April 17 through
14 April 19, 2026, and will feature delicious food, including chargrilled oysters, Tomato-a-la-
15 Chalmette, barbecue pulled pork, Cuban sandwiches, tacos, crawfish, fried rice, pizza,
16 hamburgers, and more; the annual Miss, Teen, and Junior Pageant and the Tomato Festival
17 Children's Pageant each take place on April 18; and
18 WHEREAS, the Tomato Festival will also feature live entertainment and a collection
19 of carnival rides and game booths, and its theme is "Rock of Ages"; and
